    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka ex-MP Ranjan Ramayanake leaves prison, job offered",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka former MP Ranjan Ramanayake, who received a conditional presidential pardon, has left the Welikada prison in Colombo and has also been offered a position as goodwill ambassador for migrant workers.",
        "A large crowd had gathered outside the Welikada prison complex to welcome the popular actor-turned-politician who had been imprisoned over charges of contempt of court.",
        "Shouts of \u201cRanja! Ranja!\u201d (his nickname) were heard as he came out of the prison gates Friday August 26 afternoon.",
        "Meanwhile, Minister of Labour and Foreign Employment Manusha Nanayakkara, one of Ramanayake\u2019s former colleagues in the main opposition Samagi Jana Balawegaya (SJB) who lobbied for his release, has offered him a job.",
        "\u201cI just offered [Ramanayake] a position as goodwill ambassador to promote Sri Lankan migrant worker welfare globally and he gladly accepted,\u201d Nanayakkara tweeted Friday afternoon.",
        "I just offered @RamanayakeR a position as a goodwill ambassador to promote Sri Lankan migrant worker welfare globally upon his release and he gladly accepted. This is a voluntary position to make use of his tacit knowledges in the area of foreign employment pic.twitter.com/Zqz7BqcNMz",
        "Ramanayake has been vocal about migrant worker rights and was actively, albeit unsuccessfully, involved in efforts to save the life of a Sri Lankan domestic worker who was executed in Saudi Arabia.",
        "Sri Lanka president signs conditional pardon for ex MP Ranjan Ramanayake",
        "Ramanayake left prison on Friday having served over one and a half years of a four-year sentence.",
        "The Supreme Court sentenced the former main opposition Samagi Jana Balavegaya (SJB) parliamentarian to four years\u2019 rigorous imprisonment on January 12, 2021, over contempt of court charges, in connection with disparaging remarks he had allegedly made about the judiciary in August 2017.",
        "Opposition and SJB leader Sajith Premadasa had previously written to former President Gotabaya Rajapaksa appealing for a presidential pardon for Ramanayake. The pardon never came, though Rajapaksa controversially pardoned murder-convict and former MP Duminda Silva, drawing criticism from the the Office of the United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights (OHCHR) and others. (Colombo/Aug26/2022)"
      ],
